<li><span class="citation book">Stroomer, Harry (1995). <i>Textes berbères des Aït Souab (Anti-Atlas) recueillis par le capitaine Jean Podeur, édités et annotés</i>. Aix-en-Provence: Edisud.</span><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Textes+berb%C3%A8res+des+A%C3%AFt+Souab+%28Anti-Atlas%29+recueillis+par+le+capitaine+Jean+Podeur%2C+%C3%A9dit%C3%A9s+et+annot%C3%A9s&amp;rft.aulast=Stroomer%2C+Harry&amp;rft.au=Stroomer%2C+Harry&amp;rft.date=1995&amp;rft.pub=Aix-en-Provence%3A+Edisud&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Shilha_language"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><span class="citation book">Stroomer, Harry (2001). <i>An anthology of Tashelhiyt Berber folktales (South Morocco)</i>. (Berber Studies, vol. 2). Köln: Rüdiger Köppe.</span><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=An+anthology+of+Tashelhiyt+Berber+folktales+%28South+Morocco%29&amp;rft.aulast=Stroomer%2C+Harry&amp;rft.au=Stroomer%2C+Harry&amp;rft.date=2001&amp;rft.pub=%28Berber+Studies%2C+vol.+2%29.+K%C3%B6ln%3A+R%C3%BCdiger+K%C3%B6ppe&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Shilha_language"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><span class="citation book">Stroomer, Harry (2002). <i>Tashelhiyt Berber Folktales from Tazerwalt (South Morocco). A Linguistic Reanalysis of Hans Stumme's Tazerwalt Texts with an English Translation</i>. (Berber Studies, vol. 4). Köln: Rüdiger Köppe.</span><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Tashelhiyt+Berber+Folktales+from+Tazerwalt+%28South+Morocco%29.+A+Linguistic+Reanalysis+of+Hans+Stumme%27s+Tazerwalt+Texts+with+an+English+Translation&amp;rft.aulast=Stroomer%2C+Harry&amp;rft.au=Stroomer%2C+Harry&amp;rft.date=2002&amp;rft.pub=%28Berber+Studies%2C+vol.+4%29.+K%C3%B6ln%3A+R%C3%BCdiger+K%C3%B6ppe&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Shilha_language"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><span class="citation book">Stroomer, Harry (October 2008). "Three Tashelhiyt Berber Texts from the Arsène Roux Archives.". In F.H.H. Kortlandt, Alexander Lubotsky, Jos Schaeken, Jeroen Wiedenhof. <i>Evidence and Counter-Evidence. Essays in Honour of Frederik Kortlandt. Volume 2: General Linguistics. (Studies in Slavic and General Linguistics)</i>. Amsterdam: Rodolpi. <a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9789042024717" title="Special:BookSources/9789042024717">9789042024717</a>. "<small>In Morocco, Berber is spoken in the Rif (Tarifit), in the Middle Atlas (Tamaziyt) and in the High Atlas, the Sous plains and the Anti-Atlas (Tasusiyt, Tashelhit), by an estimated 45% of the total population of 30 million people... Berber immigrant communities of various origins have settled in France, Belgium, the Netherlands, Germany and Israel. Of all Berber languages Tashelhit Berber is the one with the highest (estimated) number of speakers: some 8 to 9 million.</small>"</span><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Three+Tashelhiyt+Berber+Texts+from+the+Ars%C3%A8ne+Roux+Archives.&amp;rft.atitle=Evidence+and+Counter-Evidence.+Essays+in+Honour+of+Frederik+Kortlandt.+Volume+2%3A+General+Linguistics.+%28Studies+in+Slavic+and+General+Linguistics%29&amp;rft.aulast=Stroomer&amp;rft.aufirst=Harry&amp;rft.au=Stroomer%2C%26%2332%3BHarry&amp;rft.date=October+2008&amp;rft.place=Amsterdam&amp;rft.pub=Rodolpi&amp;rft.isbn=9789042024717&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Shilha_language"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
</ul>
